HD Camera for Android
HD Camera & Message App
("we," "our," or "us") operates the
HD Camera for Android
application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect the personal information you provide while using the App.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:
Device Information:
Details about your device, such as model, operating system, and unique identifiers.
Usage Data:
Information about how you interact with the App, including features used and duration of use.
Media Files:
Access to your camera and storage is necessary for capturing and saving photos and videos.
2. Permissions Required
To provide our services, the App may request the following permissions:
Camera Access:
Required for capturing photos and videos.
Storage Access:
Required to save and manage captured media files.
Network Access:
May be required for displaying ads and performing analytics.
3. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used for the following purposes:
To enable you to capture, edit, and manage photos and videos through the App.
To improve the App’s functionality and user experience.
To provide relevant advertisements based on your preferences.
4. Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services for analytics and advertising:
Google Analytics:
Helps us analyze the usage of the App.
AdMob by Google
: Displays advertisements tailored to your interests.
5. Data Security
We take appropriate security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse.
6. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
7. Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access your personal information.
Request correction or deletion of your personal data.
Object to certain types of processing, particularly concerning advertising.
8. CCPA Privacy
Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), residents of California have specific rights:
Right to Notice:
Information about the categories of personal data collected.
Right to Access:
Request access to your personal data.
Right to Deletion: Request the deletion of personal data collected.
Right to Opt-Out:
Request that your personal data not be sold to third parties.
9. Detailed Information on the Processing of Your Personal Data
Analytics: We may use third-party analytics services like Google Analytics to monitor and analyze usage patterns. You can opt out through device settings or by following Google’s instructions.
Advertising: We use advertising services like AdMob to display relevant ads based on user interaction.
10. Protection Against Malware and Network Abuse
Malware Protection:
The App is regularly scanned for malware to ensure user safety.
Network Abuse:
The App does not engage in unauthorized data transmission or network abuse.
11. Children’s Privacy
This App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the updated revision date.
13. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us:
App Name:
HD Camera for Android
Developer Name:
HD Camera & Message App
Email: musicvideotechnology@gmail.com
